get.description: This API is a login call to authenticate which will return a JSON token if the client's credentials are valid. This token needs to be included in all other consumption or list retrieval service requests.

parameters.name: clientID
parameters.description: Client ID of the login user

parameters.name: secretKey
parameters.description: Secret Key of the login user

get.description: This API is a consumption query that enables you to extract all KYC data points spread across the 5 folder categories of baseline for the BIC specified.

parameters.name: BIC
parameters.description: BIC of the entity for which the data needs to be extracted

parameters.name: lastPublishedSince
parameters.description: This is an optional delta parameter that enables you to restrict the consumption query to KYC data published after a given date (in the format YYYY-MM-DD).

400.description: Invalid BIC or entity cannot be found

get.description: This API is a consumption query that enables you to extract the KYC profile in zip data folder which includes all data points (in PDFs, json, and xml) and evidencing documents spread across the 5 folder categories of the baseline for the BIC specified. Please note this API will not include the annual report and signatory list which can be downloaded via GetKYCDocument.

parameters.name: BIC
parameters.description: BIC of the entity for which the data needs to be extracted

parameters.name: lastPublishedSince
parameters.description: This is an optional delta parameter that enables you to restrict the consumption query to KYC data published after a given date (in the format YYYY-MM-DD).

400.description: Invalid BIC or entity cannot be found

get.description: This API is a consumption query that enables you to download an evidencing document for the BIC specified.

parameters.name: documentId
parameters.description: Document identifier of the document to be downloaded

400.description: Invalid BIC or entity cannot be found

get.description: This API is a list retrieval query that enables you to extract a list of all entities which belong to your KYC group

400.description: Invalid BIC or entity cannot be found

get.description: This API is a list retrieval query that enables you to extract a list of all counterparties which granted access to your KYC group. Triggering this API will activate/re-activate the passive relationships.

400.description: Invalid BIC or entity cannot be found

token.description: This is used for authorization for subsequent API call, it is set as Bearer Token in Header
